select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'Basic science: thrombosis + hemostasis

คำถาม: coagulation system + bleeding disorders in surgery', '[{"label":"A","text":"No knowledge needed"},{"label":"B","text":"**Coagulation system + bleeding disorders — surgical relevance**: (1) **Hemostasis components**: - **Primary**: platelets + vWF + endothelium → platelet plug (BT measures; PFA-100) - **Secondary**: coagulation cascade → fibrin clot (PT — extrinsic + common; aPTT — intrinsic + common; TT — thrombin to fibrin) - **Fibrinolysis**: plasmin breaks fibrin (D-dimer); (2) **Coagulation cascade**: - **Extrinsic** (tissue factor → VIIa → X) - **Intrinsic** (XII → XI → IX → VIII → X) - **Common** (X → V → II/prothrombin → fibrin); (3) **Vitamin K-dependent factors**: II, VII, IX, X + protein C + S (warfarin affects these); (4) **Coagulopathy assessment**: - History (bleeding, family, medications, liver/renal disease) - Labs: PT/INR, aPTT, platelet, fibrinogen, D-dimer - Specialized: factor levels, vWF, mixing studies, viscoelastic (TEG, ROTEM) - TEG/ROTEM increasingly used (trauma, cardiac, hepatic) — point-of-care guides targeted product use; (5) **Inherited bleeding disorders**: - **Hemophilia A** (factor VIII deficiency) — X-linked; severity by factor level; treat: factor VIII replacement, emicizumab (HemA), gene therapy emerging - **Hemophilia B** (factor IX deficiency) — X-linked; factor IX replacement - **von Willebrand disease** (vWF deficiency) — most common inherited bleeding disorder; subtypes 1-3 (1 quantitative mild, 2 qualitative, 3 severe); treat: desmopressin (type 1 + 2A), vWF concentrate (Humate-P), gene therapy; - **Other rare**: factor XI, factor VII, etc.; (6) **Acquired coagulopathies**: - **Liver disease** — synthesis of factors; thrombocytopenia + functional issues - **Vitamin K deficiency** — malnutrition, malabsorption, antibiotic, neonatal - **DIC** — sepsis, trauma, malignancy, OB complications; consumptive; treat underlying + supportive - **Massive transfusion-related** — dilution + consumption - **Anticoagulant medications** - **uremia** — platelet dysfunction; (7) **Thrombocytopenia**: - **ITP** — autoimmune; treat: steroid, IVIG, TPO agonists (romiplostim, eltrombopag), rituximab, splenectomy selected - **TTP** — pentad (MAHA, thrombocytopenia, AKI, fever, neurological); ADAMTS13 deficiency; treat: plasmapheresis emergent, caplacizumab, immunosuppression; - **HIT (heparin-induced thrombocytopenia)** — type II IgG-mediated; thrombosis paradox; stop heparin, alternative anticoag (argatroban, bivalirudin, fondaparinux); HIT antibody testing - **DIC, sepsis, drug-induced, malignancy, infection** (8) **Hypercoagulable states**: - Inherited: factor V Leiden (most common), prothrombin G20210A, AT III deficiency, protein C/S deficiency, hyperhomocysteinemia - Acquired: APLS (antiphospholipid syndrome — lupus anticoagulant, anti-cardiolipin, anti-β2-glycoprotein), cancer-related, pregnancy, OCP/HRT, nephrotic, MPN (JAK2), PNH; (9) **Reversal agents**: - Warfarin: vitamin K + 4F-PCC (preferred over FFP) - DOAC: idarucizumab (dabigatran), andexanet alfa (Xa inhibitors), 4F-PCC alternative - UFH: protamine - LMWH: protamine (partial) - Antiplatelet: platelet transfusion (limited efficacy), DDAVP - DIC: treat underlying + product replacement; (10) **TXA (tranexamic acid)** — antifibrinolytic; reduces bleeding in: trauma (CRASH-2, CRASH-3), PPH (WOMAN trial), surgical (cardiac, ortho, GU); within 3h of bleeding ideal"},{"label":"C","text":"No coagulation testing needed"},{"label":"D","text":"Avoid all anticoagulants"},{"label":"E","text":"Single product for all bleeding"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Coagulation + hemostasis** — fundamental for surgery. **Components**: 1. **Primary hemostasis** — platelet plug formation: vWF binds collagen + GPIb on platelets; GPIIb/IIIa cross-linking via fibrinogen 2. **Secondary hemostasis** — coagulation cascade → fibrin: classic cascade intrinsic (XII, XI, IX, VIII) + extrinsic (TF + VII) → common (X, V, II) → fibrin. Modern cell-based model emphasizes initiation, amplification, propagation 3. **Fibrinolysis** — plasmin (from plasminogen via tPA) breaks fibrin → D-dimer **Lab tests**: - PT/INR — extrinsic + common (VII most sensitive — short half-life; warfarin) - aPTT — intrinsic + common (heparin) - TT — thrombin → fibrin - Fibrinogen - Platelet count + function (PFA-100, light transmission aggregometry) - Bleeding time (rarely used) - Specific factor levels - **Viscoelastic** (TEG, ROTEM) — global hemostasis at bedside; trauma + cardiac + hepatic surgery uses **Major inherited bleeding disorders**: - **Hemophilia A** (factor VIII): X-linked; severity by factor level (severe < 1%, moderate 1-5%, mild > 5%); treat factor replacement, emicizumab (bispecific antibody mimicking VIII), gene therapy emerging (valoctocogene roxaparvovec) - **Hemophilia B** (factor IX): X-linked; factor IX replacement, gene therapy emerging - **vWD**: most common inherited bleeding disorder; subtypes 1 (mild quantitative — desmopressin works), 2 (qualitative — A/B/M/N — vWF concentrate), 3 (severe deficiency — vWF concentrate) **Acquired coagulopathies in surgical patients**: 1. Liver disease — synthetic dysfunction + thrombocytopenia + functional 2. Vitamin K deficiency — malnutrition, antibiotic-related, neonatal 3. DIC — sepsis, trauma, OB complications, malignancy 4. Massive transfusion — dilutional + consumptive; manage with balanced products + TXA + calcium 5. Uremia — platelet dysfunction; DDAVP can improve **Thrombocytopenia in surgical patients**: - ITP, TTP, HIT, drug-induced, dilutional, sepsis (DIC), liver disease, marrow suppression - HIT (heparin-induced) — type II IgG-mediated; PARADOXICAL thrombosis risk; stop heparin + alternative anticoagulant (argatroban, bivalirudin, fondaparinux); 4T score guides suspicion **TXA** — game-changer in surgical bleeding: - Trauma — CRASH-2 (within 3h reduces mortality), CRASH-3 (TBI within 3h reduces head injury death) - PPH — WOMAN trial (reduces bleeding death) - Cardiac surgery — standard - Orthopedic (joint replacement) — reduces transfusion - Some urological **Hypercoagulable workup** — selected post-VTE: provoked vs unprovoked, age, family history, recurrent — testing factor V Leiden, prothrombin gene, protein C/S, AT III, APLS, homocysteine.', NULL,
  'medium', 'hemato_onco', 'review',
